  "excerpt": "<p>Export DataTools Pro metrics glossary to Notion with our direct API integration.</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-wideright\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"000000\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #000000;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/icons8-notion-250.png\" alt=\"Notion export\n\" class=\"wp-image-9924 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/icons8-notion-250.png 250w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/icons8-notion-250-150x150.png 150w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/icons8-notion-250-45x45.png 45w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>Export DataTools Pro metrics glossary to Notion with our direct API integration. This secured integration allows you to seamlessly push metrics definitions to business users making it accessible to Notion users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn more about <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/lesson/metrics-glossary-for-salesforce/\" title=\"Building Metrics Glossary for Salesforce with DataTools Pro\">DataTools Pro Metrics Glossary</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn about other <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/integrations/\" title=\"DataTools Pro Integrations for Metrics Governance\">DataTools Pro integrations</a></p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-1 one-column\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conenct DataTools Pro to Notion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 1: <a href=\"https://app.datatoolspro.com/user/notion\" title=\"DataTools Pro Notion Settings\">Access Notion settings page</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 2: Click &#8220;Connect DataTols Pro to Notion button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"cbe7df\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"722\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-12.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9978 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #cbe7df; width:313px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-12.png 722w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-12-300x131.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 722px) 100vw, 722px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 3. Proceed to grant permission from DataTools Pro to publish to Notion by clicking Next.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>IMPORTANT NOTE: </em></strong>DataTools Pro does NOT request the permission to read content from your Notion app..</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f3f5f7\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"869\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-13-869x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9979 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f3f5f7; width:286px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-13-869x1024.png 869w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-13-255x300.png 255w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-13-768x905.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-13.png 1161w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 869px) 100vw, 869px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 4- Select the appropriate option for how DataTools Pro should publish to your Notion instance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use a template provided by the developer</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This option will use a standard template to publish your metrics glossary. If you would like to preview the template we use, <a href=\"https://www.notion.so/Salesforce-Metrics-Glossary-0b04d93aeed14ce3b6311d4480d39a10\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">click here</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use a template provided by the developer</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This option will allow you to select individual pages that are granted permission to publish your metrics glossary.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f4f6f7\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"882\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-14-1024x882.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9980 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f4f6f7; width:359px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-14-1024x882.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-14-300x258.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-14-768x662.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-14.png 1091w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Using Notion Export</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 1. Open the <a href=\"https://app.datatoolspro.com/metrics\" title=\"Metrics Glossary\">Metrics Glossary</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 2. Filter the metrics glossary contents that you would like to export</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 3. Click the Notion icon to open the export dialogue</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f3f7f6\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"888\" height=\"371\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-10.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9976 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f3f7f6; width:367px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-10.png 888w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-10-300x125.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-10-768x321.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 4. Select the page that you would like to create and nest your metrics glossary.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 5. Open Notion to view your published metrics glossary.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Notes on Updating your Metrics Glossary</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you publish your Metrics Glossary, DataTools pro will keep a list of all pages you have published but will not automatically update Notion as you update your metrics. You will need to re-publish to post updates to users in Notion. </p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n"
}